items.sentence: I don't know if Tom still lives in Australia.
I didn't want to go to Australia without Tom.
How long did it take Tom to get to Australia?
I'm not the one who convinced Tom to do that.
I wouldn't have done that the way Tom did it.
It seems that Tom doesn't plan on doing that.
If I hadn't done that, someone else would've.
I'm sure Tom said he was planning to do that.
I would've done that myself if I'd known how.
I wonder if we're really supposed to do that.
